The article discusses the issue of fraud and identity theft in emergency benefit programs during the pandemic and proposes a three-part Pandemic Anti-Fraud proposal by President Biden. The first part focuses on empowering law enforcement to prosecute and recover money from those engaged in major fraud, providing them with the necessary time and resources. The second part emphasizes investing in fraud prevention and stopping identity theft in government benefits systems, which have been vulnerable to attacks. The third part involves a major investment in helping victims of identity theft, providing enhanced support and assistance. The proposal aims to address the systemic fraud that occurred during the pandemic and protect innocent Americans who were victims of identity theft.